news.title: Ahmedabad civic body opens fresh registrations for nine properties
news.para: In earlier rounds, lack of competition and single bids forced the civic body to cancel deals. This time, they are banking on better market response.

news.title: Uttar Pradesh government plans new building bylaws to boost urban growth
news.para: Relaxing the rules for property owners, a building plan or map certified by a licensed professional (architects) will be approved without much hassle.

news.title: Telangana RERA directs developer to rectify defects at Saket Pranamam retirement home
news.para: A key issue raised was the formation of a cooperative society, which the complainants argued was in breach of Clause 19(a) of the original agreement.

news.title: Puravankara reports pre-sales of ₹5,006 crore in FY25
news.para: Puravankara's collections were at ₹3,937 crore in FY25, reflecting a nine per cent year-on-year growth compared to ₹3,609 crore recorded in FY24. Collections for Q4 FY25 stood at ₹946 crore.

news.title: Maharashtra RERA to prioritise complaints of homebuyers suffering from terminal illnesses
news.para: Under the new system, all standard complaints will be heard strictly in chronological order based on their filing date, eliminating the perception of favouritism or undue influence.

news.title: Infosys BPM leases 1.3 lakh sq ft ft office space in Pune's Hinjewadi
news.para: The leased office space is spread over five floors spanning two commercial towers at Embassy Tech Zone, part of Embassy Office Parks REIT, showed documents accessed through realty data analytics platform Propstack.

news.title: DLF to sell its IT SEZ in Kolkata to Srijan Realty for ₹693 crore
news.para: The sale comprises of freehold land parcel admeasuring ~25.90 acres along with constructed building-DLF Tech Park with a gross leasable area of 10,54,357 sq ft.

news.title: ED raids builders in Rs 50 crore money laundering case in Hyderabad
news.para: According to ED officials, the total alleged fraud amounts to approximately 50 crore. Searches were carried out at Satish Gupta's office in Motinagar and his residence in Film Nagar, while Surana's residence in Secunderabad and his office on SP Road.

news.title: Telangana RERA warns public against Krithika Infra developers project in Boduppal
news.para: According to authority, complainants alleged that despite paying full or partial amounts for plots in the project, sale deeds were neither executed nor registered by the promoters.

news.title: House prices in UK rise 5.4% in February 2025
news.para: Average house prices rose by an annual 5.4% to 268,000 pounds ($355,556) in February, the fastest increase since December 2022 and up from a 4.8% increase in January, the Office for National Statistics said.

news.title: Rajkot civic body receives Rs 23 crore advance property tax payments after discount scheme
news.para: According to RMC, it received advance property tax and water charges amounting to Rs 23.19 crore from 44,404 taxpayers. Of this, payment of Rs 19 crore was received online.

news.title: China's new home prices remains unchanged in March 2025
news.para: China's flat home prices in March was a slight improvement from February, when prices fell 0.1% month-on-month, Reuters calculations based on National Bureau of Statistics (NBS) data showed on Wednesday.

news.title: ED raids at multiple locations in Hyderabad in money laundering case
news.para: The owner of Sai Surya Developers, Kancharla Satish Chandra Gupta, is facing a police probe for alleged delivery default of a project named 'Green Meadows'.

news.title: Smartworld Developers invests ₹1,200 crore to develop Trump Residences in Gurugram
news.para: Smartworld will be responsible for the development, construction and customer service of the project. Tribeca Developers, the official representatives of the Trump brand in India, will lead the design, marketing, sales and quality PMC.

news.title: SEBI flags ₹43 crore DLF's apartment deal in Gensol Engineering probe
news.para: SEBI probe revealed that loan proceeds meant for electric vehicle procurement were routed to purchase a ₹43 crore luxury apartment from DLF’s "The Camellias" project in Gurugram.

news.title: Families protest over unfulfilled land allotment promise in Mangaluru
news.para: Back in 2018, under the leadership of MLA Bharath Shetty, 97 families from the Kuppepadavu gram panchayat were issued title deeds and promised sites.

news.title: Nagpur civic body's town planning department nets Rs 414.52 crore revenue
news.para: This record income, collected through various fees and premiums, marked a huge leap in the department's performance, with a majority of the collections made through online transactions.

news.title: Uttarakhand HC halts construction without map around Rispana and Bindal rivers
news.para: The directive came during a hearing on multiple public interest litigations (PILs) concerning encroachment and environmental degradation in riverine areas of Dehradun and surrounding regions.

news.title: Need robust partnerships to revamp Mumbai’s housing stock: Sanjeev Jaiswal, CEO, MHADA
news.para: Redevelopment is not merely about constructing new buildings—it’s about viability, transparency, and timely delivery. A clear FSI framework and honest communication are key to safeguarding both tenant rights and project feasibility," said Sanjeev Jaiswal, CEO, MHADA.

news.title: MCG councillors seek construction waste plants in each zone in Gurugram
news.para: The councillors apprised Garg about the widespread issue of C&D waste being dumped haphazardly throughout the city and demanded "dedicated collection and processing units."
